<p class="indent3" style="-uslm-lc:I14" xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">The term “period of nonqualified use” means any period (other than the portion of any period preceding <date date="2009-01-01">January 1, 2009</date>) during which the property is not used as the principal residence of the taxpayer or the taxpayer’s spouse or former spouse.</p>
